dataIdInfo.idPurp: On and off-street bikeways, suggested routes and other connections found on the Toronto Cycling Map.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Toronto Cycling Map shows marked bicycle lanes, sharrows, signed bicycle routes and off-road paths. It also shows suggested routes and connections in areas where routes have not yet been designated as part of the Bikeway Network. The suggested routes and connections have been identified in consultation with experienced Toronto cyclists and the Toronto Cycling Advisory Committee.

Consts.useLimit: Source must be credited. Cannot be re-sold

Even/Odd address numbers on right side of street

Linear Name in full, e.g. Don Mills Rd
Numeric lowest number on the left
Intersection id at the from node
Intersection id at the to node
0 for non-oneway, 1 follow digitized direction, -1 against digitised direction
